Yeah, an island as large as the continental US and smart enough to have shut its borders down before anyone had the chance to try and make it back here with the bug. Which, BTW, plenty are still trying to do. Nearly all of the present cases of covid are from returnees in quarantine. Or, from people that have, somehow, managed to make it past the restrictions. Lucky, they're few and far between. But, the last thing we need in Australia is a situation like in the US, India or Brazil where people just ignore all the advice given to them and then hang about in crowds. India just had 400000 cases confirmed in one day!!! The US is still in a dicey position, but you're lucky enough to have a decent vaccination campaign going on. Just a population of ignorant idiots who barely function in society that are making things worse both for themselves and others. That's where mandatory vaccinations should come into force. It drags them kicking and screaming into line, whether they like it or not. And, if you mention constitutional rights, don't go there because your own government doesn't even bother with it, in the best of times. They break it all the time, for their own benefit. The whole problem is we have people, basically sociopaths, who have little regard for public safety and care more for money than anything else. You end up like India, or worse, and you won't have an economy. Just allow people to do their own thing and it's exactly the consequences that come of such decisions. Individuals may be smart and conscientious, but people in general act like ignorant idiots and don't care about the consequences of their actions. Politicians tend to be in that latter group and that's something I know from experience. What this pandemic has uncovered is just how vulnerable the present economic system is to events such as this. And, how mercenary some people can be when it comes to people's lives or money.

Ich war bei der BW wehrplichtiger, W15.
Waehrend der grundausbildung in Germasheim wurde man auf meinen werdegang aufmerksam, mutter British und 10 jahre im UK gelebt.
Wurde daraufhin zur Fernmeldeweitverkehrskompanie, einer Nato einheit, in Euskirchen versetzt.
Neben bei....die Big Band der BW, damals unter der leitung von Guenther Noris, waren unsere nachbarn, da wurde so manche party gemacht.
Wie damas so ueblich musten meine sprachkenntnisse geprueft und amtlich bestaetigt werden.
Hatte aber seinen grund....schon waehrend der grundausbildung hatte der MAD angefangen mich ein wenig auszuschnueffeln....lol
Nachdem mir eine sicherheits stufe zuerkannt wurde gings fuer 3 wochen nach Holland zum fernschreiber lehrgang und dann zu meiner eigentlichen verwendung.
Ich sass mit immer einem Uffz im fernschreibe bunker....alles sehr geheim....4 eys only!!
An manchen tagen gabs ein dutzend ferngeticker hin und her, 90min. arbeit.
Hab mir mathe unterlagen von der TU Berlin zukommen lassen und fleisig mathe studiert.
Von Uetersen und vor allem Hamburg sah ich nichts....leider.
Wollte 3 tage urlaub nehmen um mir Hamburg anzuschauen.....NO WAY......dienstreise ist nun mal dass!!!!
Nix mit fun....lol
Von der sprachen schule war ich sehr beeindruckt.
Meine US prueferin meinte nach 5 minuten....I'm not sure what are you doing here, but we have to go through the motions.....und das hiess 90min. im sprachlabor.
Wow
Hatte sowas noch nie gesehen, weder im UK noch im deutschen schulbetrieb.....when only the very best will do!
Klar
Ne schraube fuer ne F4 hat 500 dollar bei den Amis gekostet, um die ecke gerade mal 30 pfennige....lol....kleiner schertz.
Damals hatte die BW wohl kohle ohne ende.
Mir als W15er gings sau gut....als Nato einheit erhielten wir zoll und steuer freie zigarretten und alkohol...ich hatte meine eigene Uffz stube.....und marschiert bin ich in 12 monaten zur kantine und zurueck ins bett.....lol
Tolle zeit!!!!
Aber neben der romantic, die hier in der doku vermittelt wird, habe ich auch einige sehr traurige schicksale erlebt.
Z 12ler die nicht als berufsoldaten uebernommen wurden...ganz schlimmer alkohol missbrauch....und enorm hohe scheidungsraten.....all dies vor allem in den Uffz raengen.
Na ja.
Danach
Studium der electrotechnic an der TU Berlin.....Job mit Siemens.....nach Australien fuer ein 18 mth. project....verliebt ( in eine Britin, naturally)....geheiratet.....kinder.....firma gegruendet.....und nun lebe ich seit 4o jahren im tropischen norden Australiens.
Such is life.

How about this for a game design. Kudos to anyone who reads the whole thing.

I would enjoy playing as overpowered Saitama, but it would eventually feel too effortless and unrewarding. This seems to be the main problem with a One Punch Man game. If a game is made, I reckon it should begin with Saitama before his 3 year training and over time you get stronger by progressing the story, completing tasks and hunting threats in a free roam world. But you have a stat limit which can only increase with the completion of each act/progressing through the 3 years. You reach max at the end of the third year when you defeat the final enemy boss which then allows players two options. The first option is to continue free roam as an overpowered Saitama that defeats all the enemies effortlessly with endlessly generated threats and tasks. The second option is to enter a "New Game +" equivalent to dark souls where you start from the beginning again and carry over your stats but are given a new limit (increases with progress of "New Game +") and enemies are tough enough to match you again.

That way, players are rewarded for the effort of building up an unbeatable Saitama when they finish a play through and can enjoy beating everything with one punch. But when they no longer want effortless game play and desire a challenge again, they can begin a "New Game +". It should allow multiple, additional restarts (New Game +2, New Game +3, New Game +4 etc.) with each completion of a "New Game +" and with each restart, the limit is increased and the enemies get tougher. However, there should be a limit on the number of times a single game can enter "New Game +", ( I would say "New Game +7" is a good maximum). Fighting techniques like movement speed, higher defense, accuracy, Strength, health etc. should be possible to increase as a stat (individually limited by progress).

Although there is a max limit for each Game, environmental effects from fighting should increase in magnitude as stats go up. The environmental effects should not be affected by progress in a play through, but increase directly with stats to give players the feeling that they are still improving and getting stronger with each "New Game +".


Examples of effects as stats increase:
-When stats are at 12.5% (Max limit for a New Game)
Saitama's strongest punch down a street creates a rush of air that shifts cars and loose objects.

Saitama's jump leaves a mid sized crater.


-When stats are at 25% (Max limit for a New Game +)
Saitama"s strongest punch down a street additionally shatters windows.

Saitama's jump leaves a larger crater.


-When stats are at 100% (Max limit for a New Game +7)
Saitama's strongest punch can wipe out a massive chunk of the city/land into ruble. (I'm sure Saitama's actual strongest punch is probably much more damaging but in this case, the game needs to run smoothly)

Saitama's jump would cripple and collapse a building should he jump of the roof of one.


For now, the closest game I can think of to a One Punch Man simulator is "Prototype 1 and 2".

Please let me know what you think.

@@F1DD3 Ja, Sie kÃ¶nnen nicht wissen, woher eine Person kommt und das kann auch niemand von Ihnen verlangen. Aber wenn es Worte gibt, von denen generell bekannt ist, dass Sie ein hohes Verletzungspotential haben und zwar nicht nur fÃ¼r ein einzelnes Individuum, sondern fÃ¼r alle Individuum einer Gruppe (und dazu gehÃ¶rt "Zigeuner" nun mal, wo Sie potentiell 12-14 Millionen Menschen damit verletzten kÃ¶nnten), dann wÃ¤re es ratsam, einfach dieses Wort nicht zu verwenden, zumal Sprache ja sowieso immer im Wandel ist und das Wort "Roma" ja schon bekannt ist. Und dass sich die Roma durch das Z-Wort verletzt fÃ¼hlen, scheint mir mit Blick auf die Geschichte dieses Wortes sehr nachvollziehbar.
Anders formuliert: Jemand, der noch nie gehÃ¶rt hat, dass das Z-Wort ein Problem ist und es daher verwendet - das scheint mir o.k. Und zwar genau so lange, bis er es gehÃ¶rt hat. Denn dann wird der Gebrauch des Wortes zu einer bewussten Entscheidung: mir ist es dann wichtiger, das Wort (obwohl ich dessen Geschichte kenne und das mir eigentlich gar nicht besonders viel bedeutet) ganz unreflektiert weiterzuverwenden und es ist mir egal, falls ich jemanden damit verletze. Find ich nicht cool.

Zu Ihrer zweiten Frage: Warum darf ich jemanden, der sich selber als Nigga bezeichnet, nicht auch als Nigga bezeichnen. Das ist ne komplizierte Frage. Auch hier lÃ¤sst sich natÃ¼rlich die Geschichte miteinbeziehen. Die Sklaven in Amerika bzw. deren Nachfahren haben das Ihnen als Ausdruck der Erniedrigung zugestandene Wort teilweise proaktiv selber verwendet und es mit einer neuen Bedeutung aufgeladen. Dies ist ein Akt des Widerstandes gegen die UnterdrÃ¼ckung bzw. die Geschichte der UnterdrÃ¼ckung: wenn ich das Wort, dass meine Unterordnung ausdrÃ¼ckt, verwende, um eine eigenstÃ¤ndige IdentitÃ¤t daraus zu bilden, kehre ich die MachtverhÃ¤ltnisse um bzw. ich signalisiere, dass ich mich nicht weiter beherrschen lasse, dass ich eben gerade kein Sklave mehr bin. Es ist quasi eine Parodie der eigenen TragÃ¶die (ganz Ã¤hnlich wie jÃ¼dscher Humor funktioniert). Aber logischerweise funktioniert das nur, wenn ich von dieser TragÃ¶die mehr oder weniger direkt betroffen bin. Schwierig wird es, sobald Aussenstehende diesen Sprachgebrauch Ã¼bernehmen wollen.
(und das bleibt auch dann schwierig, wenn Sie das aus ganz sympathischen GrÃ¼nden tun - wie z.B. dem Versuch einer Identifikation) Warum bleibt es schwierig: weil die Geschichte der Verwendung des Begriffes bei den Aussenstehenden fehlt und damit die ganze komplexe Umkehr von Macht und Widerstand dann nicht mehr funktioniert.
Und tatsÃ¤chlich bin ich an diesem Punkt mit Ihnen einverstanden: In der Hip-Hop-Kultur gibt es dann tatsÃ¤chlich Bezeichnungen die eigentich schon problematisch zu beginnen werden und so problematische Herrschaftsstrukturen fortschreiben.
Aber das alles Ã¤ndert letztlich nichts an der Tatsache, dass das N-Wort & das Z-Wort Worte sind, die eine Geschichte haben, die von Trauma und systematischem und langjÃ¤hrigen Machtmissbrauch geprÃ¤gt sind. Und es gibt nicht viele andere Worte, von denen man das mit Ã¤hnlichem Recht sagen kann. Daher verzichte ich persÃ¶nlich lieber auf diese Worte.

If I were you, I would stop taking K2. 

If you're getting enough K1, your body can convert it to K2. There are two thoughts on this: 1) the MK-7 form of K2 can be made in the gut (if you refrain from irritants like garlic, ginger, spicy foods, tea, pepper, alcohol, etc.) but this form appears to contribute minimally to overall vitamin K status, and 2) the conversion of K1 into the MK-4 form of K2 (the one that does the heavy lifting) occurs in the testes, pancreas, and arterial walls and is independent of the gut (but this doesn't mean it's okay to eat things like garlic et al because they do interfere with B12 production).

Plus, eating too much overt fats high in PUFAs could also deplete antioxidants, including the K vitamins (Poly Unsaturated Fatty Acids).

So far I find no data that says if you take D3 to maintain your 25(OH)D level, you must take K2 with it. Yes, one of K's roles is to transfer calcium from blood and deposit it into bone, and yes, D is needed for bone health, and that's where the association was assumed, but correlation is not the same as causation. And by-the-way, the bone health mechanism is not the same as the enamel health mechanism (because enamel gets nothing directly from the blood supply). So K2 is needed by the body, but D has other co-factors (companion nutrients) that are more problematic, like magnesium, zinc, and boron. And even sufficient iodine plays a role, and many people have an iodine insufficiency. And since these minerals and elements are \essential\"

I made this beat while in a hotel which was about 200m away from Kreuzberg, one of the hardest gangster/clan/mafia districts in Berlin, Germany.

Yes, 2020 was the first year I didnâ€™t have any shows at all. It was really strange and it was disappointing because one of them would have been a solo show. I was just lucky I didnâ€™t produce any of the prints yet or I would have lost quite a bit of money. In general I was quite lucky with that in mind, I have musician friends who lost several tens of thousand in a week because their whole tour fell through. And it affects them even now because the royalties from the shows is money that is missing this year too. All while selling records and merch became even more complicated because of international shipping rates. In general the creative industries were hit really hard and we didnâ€™t get much support. It was better in some countries than in others, but here it was definitely ridiculous.

Iâ€™m lucky that I have such a supportive audience and that people care enough to help out when things get really tough. It might not be able to change my situation to one where Iâ€™m less at risk, but at least this support allows me to continue what I do as best as I can given the difficult circumstances! Thatâ€™s already quite a lot and Iâ€™m very grateful for it! And itâ€™s also the reason why I keep making videos, because it confirms that there are people out there who care! Turns out my husband was right: The people who disagree with me on these issues are not in the majority or this video would have a very different likes to dislikes ratio and a lot more anti lockdown comments! I knew there would be some people who disagree and they all have their own reasons. I know that certain people are terrified of being alone or locked in because of previous trauma. Some are very prone to depression if they arenâ€™t continually surrounded by people. And with a government as uncaring as for example the one in the US they are terrified that they are going to end up homeless because they live in a society that is broken beyond repair. In civilised countries this wouldnâ€™t even cross their minds because their healthcare would be covered, the government would offer them housing for free in times of need and theyâ€™d even get free food delivered to their door by the government when in quarantine. These are all things communist countries did during this crisis, but certain people have lived in a cut throat capitalist dystopia where they have to GoFundMe their healthcare for such a long time that they donâ€™t even want to believe that a different way of life is possible.

I grew up in a socialist country. Even though not everything was good I never had to go hungry, I always had a roof over my head - it wasnâ€™t always a good roof, but it was a roof that I was guaranteed to have - my education was free, my healthcare was free and I had a right to a job when I grew up. And my parents could send a 6 year old child alone on public transport through half the city without worrying that anything would happen to me. And then capitalism came and my world turned into a hellhole because suddenly the whole neighbourhood was unemployed, which lead to violence and despair. And then 25% of the population left turning one of the major cities in the region into a ghost town. My project Progress through Demolition is about that. No, before the wall came down I couldnâ€™t have bananas whenever I wanted them. But at least I never had to worry that I might end up on the street without healthcare or food in the middle of a pandemic or that my government would let me die for profit.

I just donâ€™t think people in the US get what socialism is about because theyâ€™ve been told so many lies about it. Socialism is about caring for your population enough for them never to go hungry or without a roof or without access to education. And itâ€™s about not allowing a situation to happen where part of the population is sacrificed for profit. Of course nobody in power in the US wants people to know that socialism is all about that, because US citizens might actually demand something like that for themselves!

Yes I agree. It definitely is.
I mean, I for example do love the fact, that Pyra and Mythra are in the Game and I cannot wait for them to be released. However, this whole argument became a farce very fast, as you have seen in the video. People bring up stupid points and claim to have the right "moral" to say, what they think, even without realizing that their arguments is worth JACK SHIT.

In most arguments, people bring up this "feminism" shit, which I hate for example. Bringing up 1 or 2 points without actually proven facts is just stupid. If you ever dare to have a different opinion, than these people, they hunt you down like WITCH.
I see many STRAIGHT people actually enjoy Shirtless Sephiroth / Shulk. I am not offended or anything by it. But if we bring actually 2 really sexy female characters into the game, which have MORE CLOTHE than any other female, I agree to disagree on the argument;
Sexy or not - I enjoy the fact, that Pyra and Mythra are in the game, cause I bounded with these two over the course of over 180 hours. Mythra is my girl here.
Still, people (mostly feministic idiots) point out the only thing, they can see, why Pyra and Mythra are catered to a more Xenoblade Fanbase audience.
Xenoblade is a beloved Series and I picked it up and actually enjoyed it.
Hell, I played the game as critical as I possibly could. The first time I encountered "Brighid" one of the female characters I thought to myself "Yep there is the Eye-Candy" she was really sexy designed. But over the course of 20 hours in, I actually saw past all these "Sexy" designes and enjoyed the game for its interactions between the characters more and more. Every Lead-Cast member has an engaging story and my MOST FAVOURITE character isn't even a female AT ALL:
Here my top 5 list:
1st: Tora - He is a literal weeb and so funny to see him in situations, where his "weeb-side" sticks out.
2nd: Moragh - Is the moralistic military female character, who wants to bond with her brother more, so they can have better conversations and needs to find her OWN sense of life and what it means to find one.
3rd: Pyra is a cute, nice girl that is together with Rex because of the GUILT she feels.
4th: Mythra is at the beginning a real tsundere, but warms up to Rex over the whole game.
5th: Zeke is first a comedy-release character but becomes BAD-ASS during the mid-section of the game.

Every character is so damn well written - I love it!
I'm not saying you should play the game, if you don't want to, but you definitely miss out :D

To summ it up:
Feminism is about double standards and they don't even want to understand you while wallowing in their own despair.

Regarding the Peavey amp you had. I had the 20 watt piranha head and all it did was fuzz all of the time. A buddy of mine who repairs amps said it was the power section. A lot of the newer Peaveys tend to humm alot. They have cheap chinese transformers made with blueprints for American electrical systems. The wiring/earthing in shops is usually sufficient to cancel the humm but house wiring can be sub par. With amps like Orange and Marshall the power section has better earthing and is equipped for changes in voltage. He said a lot of the newer American amps make noise on our (European) electrics. Hope all goes well with the Marshall. Take care.

The Philippines has traditionally let refugees in throughout history, the Jews were just one of several persecuted people that sought refuge in the country. Almost unknown in the English-speaking world, Johannes Heesters had an amazing career. He last appeared as a singer aged 108. His sight had gone and when acting he memorized his lines. Married to his first wife for 55 years, soon after her death he tied the knot again in his 90s- to an actress half his age.

He was a Dutchman who was never forgiven for continuing to film in Germany after the Netherlands was occupied, and for schmoozing innocently with Hitler. But he was no Nazi, and after the war he remained a huge star in Adenauer's Germany, showered with awards. Like others, such as Marika Rokk and Zarah Leander, he ought to be publicized more widely.

Genau das gleiche hab ich auch gedacht und hab mir mal angeguckt welches Material Mercedes verwendet. Herausgekommen ist folgendes: Mercedes baut eingefÃ¤rbte Plastikteile ein, es ist nur Klavierlack Optik , an sich ist es aber stink normaler schwarzer Kunststoff, der keinen Lack hat und deshalb unheimlich schnell zerkratzt (keine Versieglung). Habe mir dann die Klavierlack optik im BMW 5er angeguckt (SA) und sofort hat man den unterschied gemerkt. BMW trÃ¤gt echtes Holz auf und versiegelt es mit echtem schwarzen Lack, wie bei einem echten Piano eben. Daher ist die schwarzlack Optik bei Mercedes Basesausstattung (extrem billig) und bei BMW eine Sonderausstattung (deutlich aufwendiger, kostspieliger). Bei gebrauchten C Klassen etc. im Internet findet man ja fast nur noch diese billige Klavierlack Optik. Auch Mercedes ist wohl qualitativ nicht mehr die Marke die sie einmal wahr.

There is no such thing as PINOY BAITING!

FILIPINOS in general are naturally appreciative about the videos that VLOGGERS are creating about the Philippines....The Filipinos are INTELLIGENT AND SMART ENOUGH if they are being taken advantage of OR being used by the content creators for the sake of views and money!

Filipinos are such BEST FANS AND SOLID SUPPORTERS most especially if they feel that the channel is uplifting them as individuals with dignity and respect!

I would rather watch a channel that shows appreciation and happiness about my country rather than to watch certain vlogs that is only HIGHLIGHTING AND ROMANTICIZING the CORRUPTION in the Philippine government, the war against DRUGS, PROSTITUTION, INEQUALITY and POVERTY.

I mean the Filipinos are already aware of those TIMELESS ISSUES and they are SICK and TIRED of these kinds of videos that will only make them feel a HOPELESS CASE!

We maybe watching a lot of REACTION channels not because of global validation but I guess the better term would be "acknowledgement and acceptance".

Don't get me wrong though.
We don't need validation because the Filipinos already know what they are capable of doing and they know their worth.

It would just be hard to blame us if we get excited and thrilled if people abroad or other countries would notice us for different reasons especially having to go through a series of invasion and SHAME from the hands of the Spaniards for almost 400 years, was used and discriminated by the Americans for decades and raped and beaten to death by the Japanese soldiers.

If the reactors are using exaggerated thumbnails on their video or using the Philippine flag, then it shouldn't be an issue. I don't see anything WRONG with it for as long as the video does not ruin the things that it talks about the country. That is what you call MARKETING STRATEGY!

Clickbait is no longer a new thing for any of us! You could try to search an online money making channel and you could actually see that those channels would throw LOADS OF CASH on their thumbnails as a way to attract viewers! SAME GOES WITH REACTION CHANNELS!

The people in this country could make a channel or an organization famous but please bear in mind that Filipinos could also bring it down if they see no reasons to watch it!

Again, Filipinos can be your best friend but they could also be your worst nightmare if they feel that you are just using them for the sake of fame and money!

They watch good vlogs and REACTION channels not because of global validation but they support these channels simply because they share about the good and cool stuff in the Philippines to make others aware that a good country like us exists!

In practical and business sense, why would someone react to a video that will disappoint them? We can't blame content creators if they find Filipino cover songs better than the original.

As long as the channel is real and authentic with their views then Filipinos know how to pay it back with their deserved viewership!

Message to reaction haters though...
If you don't like REACTION channels then don't subscribe to it and don't watch it! Nobody is forcing you to do so!.
That's how simple it is!
It's a FREE COUNTRY!
Just sayin'!

Salute to all foreign legitimate VLOGGERS who genuinely love the Philippines and make the effort to make a difference!

Making it Happen, Juicy Vlog, Finding Tom, Finn Snow, Becoming Filipino, Happiness Crossing, Dwaine Wooley, Bret Maverick, Nas Daily, Puting Pinoy, Bisayang Hilaw, 8 Miles from home, EAP films and the rest.

If you don't know what the transmission of my key fob is that acts as a proximity switch to allow me to unlock my car door by touching the handle of the car door just go away.

Just to let you know, the signal is already produced or echoed back in the case of a RFID, and making a device to recognize the exact digital pattern of my FOB is no less secure than my car door already is.

In fact since its hand made and keyed specifically to my FOB, the idea that someone would think my house door works that way is ridiculously improbable. ( Along with my masters degrees, I have a undergraduate degree in Mathematics. The issue here is to know what the XMIT of my car door FOB is write a Rasberry PI program to recognize what that pattern is and when it does it arms the unlock button.

NOW, I haven't taken the battery out of my key FOB yet, but I"m 90% sure that if I do I could still have my car unlock automatically. That would confirm my belief that the unlock feature that only works when I'm within 1-2 meters of the car and requires no button push on the fob to open the door is in fact RFID as RFID is completely passive. (You can look up passive vs active RFID on your own time.) Having the reader of the key FOB in the vehicle gives lots of room for a high gain antenna to be built into the door so that it could reach the necessary 1-2 meters vs the systems that require you to hold a card up to the reader within a centimeter or two (like the way the disney magicband works.)

DrexlFlo Brother, this is genius....I have a small engineering metal lathe that I have been lucky enough to buy very cheaply. I already have a 50mmx2000mm belt sander that I built a year or so ago but it is completely adjustable to take anything from a 1000mm belt upto and including 4200mm, not an easy build but certainly one of my favourite builds. But the belts can run into hundreds of pounds for the high quality ones like "trizact" (I think that's the name). And I thought I would save money by building it in such a way that I can accommodate different sized belts as some go on offer all the time on ebay, but they are always different sizes!
Anyway, this video has inspired me to make something similar to what you have made, but mine will need a removable back plate, so the metal I shape will have a stable platform for shaping beveled edges etc. If you are interested I will photograph or film the progress, which if you like you could use in some content for one of your videos.

@Paap NÃµmm that's good info about the LF (you are not helping me to resist buying one by the way). There are still some SoftPops around for sale, but I am starting to see the prices climb.

In terms of clocking, you can run gate pulses into the three sockets A B and C on the back, then run mini-cables from the corresponding patch bay into some of the mod inputs like OSC 0 sync. What that does is basically to clock the cycling of OSC 0 - which continuously cycles unless you tell it not to. OSC 0's cycling in turn sets the tempo of the manual loop recorder that's attached to OSC 1. The tricky thing is that OSC 0 is still free to adjust the cycling, so what you get is various speeds that work with the input clock tempo plus some in-between speeds that are sort of chaotic.

This also makes it a challenge to do something like getting the characteristic bloops and pops to snap to the incoming tempo. They will usually happen on the overall grid of the tempo, but their precise location in time doesn't feel totally controllable. This is part of the charm of course. One of my videos called Soft Kicks is about trying to get a rhythmic kick out of Softpop - you can see how I'm struggling while also having fun. There is also the Secret Chamber on SoftPop, which can help untangle some of the unique internal normalizations.

Mit Netzwerkkabel geht es hier los:

reflector -c Germany -a 6 --sort rate --save /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist
pacman -Syy
timedatectl set-ntp true
lsblk

Partitionen erstellen:

1=+300M als ef00(EFI) 2=+2G als 8200(swap) 3=leer/leer(8300 als ext4)
also "o"=format dann "n"=neu "w"=write zum Schluss und "y"=bestÃ¤tigen

lsblk
mkfs.fat -F32 /dev/sda1
mkswap /dev/sda2
swapon /dev/sda2
mkfs.ext4 /dev/sda3 (mit "y" bestÃ¤tigen und fertig)
mount /dev/sda3 /mnt
mkdir -p /mnt/boot/efi
mount /dev/sda1 /mnt/boot/efi
lsblk
pacstrap /mnt base linux linux-firmware vim "intel-ucode" (bei AMD weg lassen, da im Paket linux-firmware enthalten)

Erster Schritt geschafft:

genfstab -U /mnt >> /mnt/etc/fstab
cat /mnt/etc/fstab

arch-chroot /mnt (nun arbeiten wir direkt im neuen System)

ln -sf /usr/share/zoneinfo/Europe/Berlin /etc/localtime
hwclock --systohc
vim /etc/locale.gen (Raute weg bei de_DE.UTF-8 UTF-8)

echo "LANG=de_DE.UTF-8" >> /etc/locale.conf
echo "KEYMAP=de_DE-latin1" >> /etc/vconsole.conf
echo "archxps" >> /etc/hostname
vim /etc/hosts

127.0.0.1 localhost
::1 localhost
127.0.1.1 archxps.localdomain archxps
passwd (Rootpasswort erstellen)
pacman -S grub efibootmgr networkmanager network-manager-applet wpa_supplicant dialog mtools dosfstools base-devel linux-headers git reflector bluez bluez-utils cups hplip xdg-utils xdg-user-dirs inetutils dnsutils bash-completion tlp powertop alsa-utils pulseaudio pulseaudio-bluetooth acpi acpi_call

grub-install --target=x86_64-efi --efi-directory=/boot/efi --bootloader-id=GRUB
grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
systemctl enable NetworkManager
systemctl enable bluetooth
systemctl enable cups
systemctl enable sshd
systemctl enable tlp
useradd -mG wheel Benutzername (Benutzer erstellen)
passwd Benutzername
usermod -c 'evtl.Echtname' Benutzername
EDITOR=vim visudo (oder nano/die /etc/sudoers.d erstellen #weg bei wheel)
exit
umount -a
reboot

@Janett Grady I have been considered mentally handicapped meaning it takes me longer to get what is meant like in mathematics. Whatever other school subjects as well . If given enough time to figure out what is meant I understand completely . Just because I am slow at somethings  I can learn things much easier,quicker when necessary . I have the willingness to learn .  People did make fun of me when I walk differently . I just happen to have weak ankles . There were times when I am very tired,don't feel my best,my ankles twist in another direction,meaning both of my ankles . Then I fall to the ground . I have have had fractured ribs on my left side . It's not funny to me when I fell, then I end up hurting . The people who laugh at me don't care to realize that when they laugh at me it'll come back on them in some way,shape,form . I don't do it on purpose or for laughs . I don't drive a vehicle of any kind, before the man I spoke of that loves me more than ever meaning before we got together I used the fixed route shuttle buses for the transportation that was necessary for me to use . Meaning to go get bills paid in full,groceries,get necessities,to come home on .  About 11 years ago they hired a new driver for the transportation I spoke of . Since I knew the routes of where they went,the times to be there to catch it I never ever forgot anything . I made quite a few friends who  were drivers . I always paid them due respect . I always done what was necessary . I never ever caused any problems at all for any of the drivers that were my friends . I always knew how to conduct myself . The people that I spoke of always thought alot me . When Christmas time was around the corner I always made out Christmas cards for each,everyone that I could think of .  I know that I couldn't give each,everyone a Christmas present . So I decided to give Christmas cards filled with love,caring,sincere thoughts of how much I cared for each & everyone I knew . I just wanted to make their Christmas better for them out of the kindness,consideration of my heart. Getting back to the driver that they hired I had pulled the cord to signal that it was my stop of where I wanted to get off the shuttle bus . Some stupid idiot that I knew for a very long time ago was on it as well . He made a high dive for the door,the drive let him go through . I hollered that he should've stop where he had . When he slammed on the brakes he knocked me to a sitting position . I had no way of holding on to the handle bars for my hands had 2 plastic grocery shopping bags full of groceries . I hit the back of the plate on the steps . I had my left foot entangled in a stroller . My right foot was entangled in a wheelchair . I was trying very hard to brace myself,it just didn't work out the way I had planned . As I got up to leave there were people who asked me if I was okay being in pain I couldn't answer them.  Believe it or not I had a premonition something was going to happen . I was correct . My tailbone was fractured . There isn't anything that can be done for that from what I was told . I called into ask information about what I felt was necessary . I had legimate questions to ask . All I was ever told by the person who answered the phone " I can't answer that " . I thought to myself " what the h can you answer " if you get my meaning . I felt entitled to answer so which I didn't get !  I tried to get some sleep for 3 1/2 days because I thought that was stubborn not to give into the pain . As it turned out I had to go to the emergency room . There I was told that I did have a fractured tailbone . I even knew it before I went to the emergency room ! I went to talk to a lawyer,i gave every bit of information possible to the lawyer that was necessary . They (the people who were at the company where the shuttle buses came from) wanted me to settle for different amounts of money,i wouldn't do it . Until I finally had to settle for the amount of what it was . I told the lawyer that no matter what the weather was like,for as long as I lived I would always be in severe pain 24 /7 . If I could've I would've taken them for every d dollar & cent they brought in on a daily basis just for the pain I had to go through .  The person who answered the phone told me that she had a sprained ankle . I thought to myself It's not anything compared to a fractured tailbone you old witch on a broom stick ! If I made you laugh at that part I at the time didn't feel like a happy camper for I was p.o. ! Come to find out there were other people hurt as well . I sure don't lie & joke when the truth needs to be known .

Max Heinrich Gutzmann LiebowÂ I've been to London but only stayed for a week with my family. We got to see the landmarks, very impressive city. Mom took me to Paris (she speaks French fluently, I am trying to learn from her). Did not care for it that much. They are not keen people who speak English with an American accent haha. I played a joke by ordering a meal from the rude waiter by speaking it in German. He didn't laugh haha. I will look for that book, it sounds interesting, thanks for the suggestion! I am not Communist, but on the other hand, I'm not a Nazi but I've read "Mein Kampf" since it was re-issued in Germany. Amazing it sold out almost as soon as it hit the shelves. Says something about the failure of the current government in Germany! I'm fine with "heavy" reading, it just takes me longer to get through it. "Mein Kampf" is a book like that. I skimmed it but haven't read it cover to cover. I'm surrounded by English, have been most of my life, but for people who only speak one language, that's the best language to speak. It's understood almost everywhere. What is your opinion about what is happening in Germany today with the refugees? I know opinions vary. :)

Wow, you've convinced me.

When someone tells me they didn't like something I made, I want to know why, I want to fix it, not hit them over the head with a hammer. Was I too mean? Probably. I could have worded it nicer. Was I right to be mean? No! Maybe I was frustrated that day, maybe I was holding back criticism for too long. If you want to take offense to that, that's entirely in your right.
You'd be a hypocrite, though, because that's exactly the same as what you did, you wanted to win the "mean YouTube comment" contest. If you'd started this conversation with "your comment was too mean", I would absolutely have toned it down, but that's not what you did. At no point before now have I personally insulted those game devs, either of you, and yet, that's the first thing you jumped to when you decided to respond to me.
I have baggage about this kind of thing, I know people who act like this in real lifeâ€” because they know they can get away with it. I'm sure you will too. You'll leave with the image that you're satisfied, that you've shown everyone that I've been put in my place. You'll have the last word, because I left to go eat breakfast or something. But I know how people like you think.

DummheitÂ bezeichnet umgangssprachlich eineÂ tÃ¶richteÂ Handlung sowie einen Mangel anÂ IntelligenzÂ oderÂ Weisheit. Im Unterschied zu anderen Bezeichnungen, die auf Mangel an Intelligenz hinweisen, bezeichnet Dummheit (alltagssprachlich) aber auch die Einstellung, nicht nur etwas nicht wahrnehmen zu kÃ¶nnen, sondern auch es nicht wahrnehmen zu wollen.







DefinitionIm engeren Sinne ist Dummheit die mangelhafte FÃ¤higkeit, ausÂ WahrnehmungenÂ angemessene SchlÃ¼sse zu ziehen beziehungsweise zu lernen. Dieser Mangel beruht teils auf Unkenntnis von Tatsachen, die zur Bildung eines Urteils erforderlich sind, teils auf mangelhafter Intelligenz oder Schulung des Geistes oder auf einer gewissen TrÃ¤gheit und SchwerfÃ¤lligkeit im AuffassungsvermÃ¶gen beziehungsweise der Langsamkeit bei der Kombination der zur VerfÃ¼gung stehenden Fakten (sieheÂ UrteilsvermÃ¶gen). In diesem Sinne nenntÂ KantÂ den â€Mangel an Urteilskraftâ€œ als â€das, was man Dummheit nenntâ€œ, und postuliert, dass â€einem solchen Gebrechen ... gar nicht abzuhelfenâ€œ sei.[1]Â Weitere Ursachen liegen im emotionalen Bereich (emotionaler Widerstand gegen Einsichten, AbhÃ¤ngigkeit von Meinungsbildnern) und in derÂ IndoktrinationÂ undÂ ManipulationÂ durch andere. The concept behind bank or some other monetary 'authority' created money first assumes that the unit of measure must precede the activity or things that will be measured. That is a false assumption. The thinking behind bank authority money assumes that the unit of measure can be \created.\" That is a false assumption. The thinking behind bank money also assumes that the bank has some Magical Power to create the unit which is assumed to necessarily precede the activity or things that will be measured. That is a false assumption. The thinking behind bank money also assumes that the unit the bank creates -Poof!- with its Magical Powers is an item of value within the rest of the real world items of value. That is a false assumption. The thinking behind bank money also assumes that these Magically Created items of 'value' are also items of property that are claimed as the property of the Magical Unit Creator and can be loaned out to others for their use but must be returned to the Magical Unit Creator. That is a false assumption. The thinking behind bank money also assumes that the Magically Created Unit can be an item of 'value' within the rest of the the real world of value and can
column5: thereby
column6: be used to measure the value of the items in the entire rest of the real world of value. That too is a false assumption And the thinking behind bank money assumes that the populace cannot actually determine that all this thinking is false and cannot come up with a way to acCount for its own activity and interaction in a different way.  That too is a false assumption.

sentiment: You may also notice that the question of 'interest' has not even been brought into this analysis. But I am guessing you already assume correctly that the need for interest is false.

hate_speech: all the above applies to both public and private banking and/or any other 'monetary authority' assumptions as to the means by which the unit of acCount comes into existence.

sentiment: The People must come to know that money creation
hate_speech: from nothing and yet turned into a thing of 'value' - Poof! - is NOT a power that anyone actually has
content: not any government
column5: not any bank.

sentiment: There is no \"authority\" or anyone else that has some magical power to create a thing of value from nothing. And if no entity has this power it certainly cannot hand this power off to the very banks that now hold even governments hostage to this process!

We all must know that the illiterate 'pre-creation' of units is different from unit creation that comes after the work is done as recognition/a record of it. We must articulate this difference to keep people aware that it is their own freely initiated enterprise that calls the use of money into existence. When we lose sight of this we lose our sovereignty.
The MSTA is not alone in the assessment that the conceptual basis and the follow on structure of money itself is wrong.
Former President of the FR Bank in Minnesota
language: proves the current definitions (and follow on assumptions about money) to be \"vacuous\" and asserts that the function of money is as a unit of measure/bookkeeping.

sentiment: â€œMy argument demonstrates the vacuity of the three standard explanations of the role of fiat money in an economy: money acts as a store of value
language: and a unit of account....The traditional explanations for the presence of money in an economy are more descriptive of its functions than explanatory. The true explanation for moneyâ€™s presence is that money is a record-keeping device.â€

sentiment: And if money is record keeping then the units themselves on the ledger sheets cannot themselves BE items of value. They are the abstract representation of the genuine goods and services of value in interactions between people.

And if money is a record keeping device whose units are used after the fact to do the recording then it clearly does not make sense that its units must pre-exist that which they will be used to record or that they must be pre-created by some magical mystical monetary unit creator

And each time its lyrics slightly changed.We don't know the authors of either the music or the text, but we know the name of the Soviet composer , who processed the romance: Maximilian Steinberg (1883- 1946).
From the moment of its appearance the song gained huge popularity."The White Acacia " sounded in the theatre play "The Days of the Turbins ".I.V.Stalin watched the play several times.
In 1976 the movie ,, The Days of the Turbins " was shot.And a new ,, The White Acacia " was composed for the film by V.Basner (music) and M. Matusovsky (lyrics). The old romance was changed by them and got the second life.
Today we have two romances ,, The White Acacia ": the song of the beginning of the 20 th century and its new variant from the movie. The second version is performed more often ..

It is extremely ignorant to proclaim all of humanity evil and all of the animal kingdom good. Remember, evil exists in all species, whether human, wolf or dog. Wolves slaughter innocent creatures on a daily basis without a shred of feeling or sympathy. They establish a society based around violence and dominance, where the weakest wolves are brutally bullied and mistreated by their fellows.

They don't care who they mate with, wolves have even been known to rape their own pups in order to reproduce. Your blind worship of these animals stuns me. I love wolves too, but I don't wish I was one and I certainly don't claim to be one.

I also don't cherrypick the behaviours of these wild creatures in order to make them sound like angels on four legs. They're not. No animal can be.

You can't just ignore the worst in wolves and the best in humans, you have to acknowledge both exist within the two species. I agree he doesn't love Shio, he has a lust for her purity, and that's the part that I consider to be his flaw (which works well thematically; he mistakes lust for love much like other characters). However, comparing him to Satou isn't a good measuring stick; she's literally a murderer and kidnapper, it's not hard to "deserve" more than her.

I disagree that someone his age would fix him. I think the issue is that rather than having someone to love, he needs someone to love him (and I don't think age is necessarily an issue). His mother fails to show enough familial love to be part of his recovery from trauma, Satou's friend doesn't care for him enough to tell his mom or call a therapist for him (and is probably too scared/creeped out to consider that), and Shio caring for him made him feel purified (not knowing it was lust and not love, hence his improvement was superficial as he simply became more obsessed and dependent). Funny that literally anyone aside from Shio (and I guess children similar to Shio) showing him enough "love" would set him on the right path.

Something I like about the series is the jar/candy symbolism for love. If I were to describe his jar when Shio pats him, I'd say he shakes his jar so excitedly for the candy he wants that none of it stays in, leaving him an empty jar that felt the sweet candy that briefly touched it, making him quick to seek more. He needs to get candy from someone that won't make him shake his jar so much; someone that gives him candy in a way that keeps him calm. The candy (love) can be from family (familial love), friends (platonic love), or a girlfriend (romantic love), but not from Shio (lust) or he'll unintentionally shake the candy out.

Der Film wurde mit DJI Mimo 3 gedreht und bearbeitet . Wir stellten uns Im Test Nr . 2 ( Rauchmodul Umbau Test Nr 2 ) die Frage , kann man aus einem Heng-Long Raucherzeugermit 7,2 Volt mehr Rauch bekommen ? Und wir waren nach einem sehr langen und beschwerten Weg nun auf dem richtigen Weg . Daraus wurde nun dieser Raucher entwickelt , der auch bei 7,2 Volt genÃ¼gend Rauch erzeugen kann , damit man ihn auch im Freien sieht . Es gildet zu beachten , daÃŸ hier in dem Video hinter dem Raucher( hinter dem Rauch ) keine schwarze Pappe gehalten wird man sieht den Rauch auch so , da das Rauchmodul genÃ¼gend dichter Rauch produziert ( es muÃŸ nichts sichtbar gemacht werden ) . Der Rauchgenerator hat nun einen grÃ¶ÃŸeren Tank , womit er mehr RauchflÃ¼ÃŸigkeit transportieren und somit lÃ¤nger in Betrieb bleiben kann . Die besonderheit an dem Rauchmodul ist , daÃŸ die AbgasschlÃ¤uche nicht geklebt wurden , diese halten durch ein AusgeklÃ¼geltes StecksÃ¼stem  somit ist der komplette Raucherzeuger sehr wartungsfreundlich . Betrieben wird der Raucher spÃ¤ter mit einer ELMOD Fusion Pro Ref. F da kann man den Rauchgenerator dann so einstellen , daÃŸ er geschwindigkeitsabhÃ¤ngig mehr und weniger Rauch ausstÃ¶ÃŸt ( das wird dann in einem anderen Film gezeigt , wenn der Rauchgenerator in einem Panzer verbaut ist )  . The film was shot and edited with DJI Mimo 3. In test no. 2 (smoke module conversion test no 2) the question, can you get more smoke from a Heng-Long smoke generator with 7.2 volts? And after a very long and difficult journey, we were now on the right track. This smoker has now been developed from this, which can generate enough smoke even at 7.2 volts to be seen outdoors. It should be noted that in the video behind the smoker (behind the smoke) there is no black cardboard. You can also see the smoke that way because the smoke module produces sufficiently thick smoke (nothing has to be made visible). The smoke generator now has a larger tank, with which it can transport more smoke liquid and thus remain in operation longer. The peculiarity of the smoke module is that the exhaust hoses are not glued, they are held by an ingenious plug-in system, so the complete smoke generator is very easy to maintain. The smoker is later operated with an ELMOD Fusion Pro Ref. F because the smoke generator can then be set so that it emits more and less smoke depending on the speed (this is shown in another film when the smoke generator is installed in a tank). See film. Kind regards .

@Ben Jacobs Hi, Ben.
Well, I donâ€™t believe in an anthropomorphised god either. The pagans do, but the Christians and the Torah-believing Jews donâ€™t, for thatâ€™s not the God described in the Bible, both the OT and the NT (Acts 17:24-25). The biblical God, being a wholly Incomprehensible Other, condescended in revealing Himself to us using our language devices. Anthropomorphism and anthropopathism are employed by the biblical authors under the inspiration of the Spirit to describe the otherwise indescribable God. And ultimately, in the Incarnation, the eternal Son of God - the Word - was made flesh, to reveal the Father to us, for He is the image of the invisible God.

I do agree with you that religions in general do promote some societal benefits, but ultimately Christianity is the only true and valid basis for all those benefits. Take morality for example, without a transcendent moral standard that is dictated by a Lawgiver, all talks about morality are but mere opinions. We are free to do as we please as thereâ€™s no moral standard by which we must abide and be judged. Islam cannot give you that basis of morality, as the god of Islam has a very skewed standard of justice. Muslims can basically commit all kinds of atrocities, but if thereâ€™s an ounce of â€œgoodnessâ€ in the so-called professors of Shahada, they would enter heaven. Thereâ€™s no atonement for sin in Islam, and the god of Islam simply doesnâ€™t care. The worldview of Oriental religions like Hinduism and Buddhism is also incompatible with morality, as everything is but an illusion; existence is the greatest evil; salvation (moksha) is described as being emancipated from existence itself. In such an illusory universe, what difference does it make whether one lives morally or immorally? Thereâ€™s neither a Lawgiver or a final judgment. Everything flows in an endless cycle of death and rebirth. Itâ€™s even worse in the case of atheism or agnosticism. If the world came to be from the Big Bang, why should â€œbags of stardustâ€ like us care about morality? If mankind is mere naturalistic, evolutionary product, survival of the fittest (the strong preying on the weak) should be the universal principle in all our social dealings. Loving our neighbours is incompatible with the evolutionary worldview. Exploiting our neighbours for personal gains should be the way to go. So you see, only Christianity can offer a basis for morality and societal betterment, for it teaches that we are all made in the image of God, and we are called to cultivate the earth for the prosperity of mankind (Genesis 1:27-28), unto the glory of God. God also gave us the Law, both in the form of the Decalogue and our inner conscience (Romans 2:12-16), that all may be judged by His perfect standard. Thatâ€™s why regardless of our religious status, we all have an innate sense of morality and justice. We simply cannot stop being the image of God, even if we deny His existence.

Btw, according to what standard do you determine something to be â€œfictitiousâ€ or â€œinherently metaphoricalâ€?

And Iâ€™m sure you do value distinctions, as the differences between things are what you consider before making any important life decisions and purchases.

Oh no, that's not the issue. If you update to the latest Windows 7 security patches it's been disabled from the GUI. You can now only format them from the command line, which means looking up the exact commands format a: /T:80 /N:9 every time I want to do it. Not very convenient!

The reason this was an issue here is that the program that I was using to make floppies from .img files had two options: 1) format disk and write image 2) write image only. The first option no longer works, so it was necessary to first format the disk from the command line, then use option 2.

As far as I can tell, Windows 7 is mostly crippled these days. The browser works intermittently, there are always problems with the floppy drivers and the thing is so slow it is almost unusable.
